rComments: His lectures are not the most interesting, but there are only 4-grade components: Reading report (30%), Term paper outline (easy 10%) - you can revise and resubmit and he gives you feedback, and the term paper (40%) if you did the outline it helps a lot. He is VERY big on participation (20%) just ask questions and respond to his questions.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: He was clearly a really nice person but was a boring lecturer. His classes were very disorganized, the readings were dense/boring and his assignments were super vague. He also didn't always answer emails or gave incomplete feedback which affected some peoples grades. If he didn't grade attendance, attending his class would've been useless.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'So many papers', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Professor Beauregard is a great professor, I'd recommend you to take his class as he turns a topic that most people find boring like cultural policy and makes it to an enjoyable topic. He encourages class discussion and provides great feedback on assignments. He was really kind throughout the semester extending the due dates for assignments.

Lectures are boring but you have to attend because participation and attendance is worth 20%. Hard marker but his feedback on assignments really helps you improve. If you attend class and read the articles you'll get an A. Make sure you have a really good thesis statement for your papers though.
Really nice prof, makes efforts and care for students. But he is just so boring and monotone... Lots of assignments but unrelated to course materials

Im not sure how he teaches in his other classes, but Professor Beauregard was an amazing professor! He made cultural policy (which might seem boring at first glance) really interesting and he was super flexible with deadlines, which was really nice. Participation is important (every class we need to submit participation questions). A solid choice!

I found the class to be disorganized and a bit all over the place. The content was very interesting, but I'm not sure the prof really knew what he was talking about. He seemed like a very kind person, I just think the class might not have been his thing. I didn't love that he attributed 20% to in-class participation, nor did he record the lectures
Very good prof! He is very good with engaging with students! He is a tough marker though, so make sure you put in 100% when doing assignments.

He took over the class halfway through the semester after our old prof "resigned" and did a great job of making the class an enjoyable one for students. His lectures are a bit boring and slow but informative and he explains things clearly. Only bad thing I have to say is he is kinda a hard marker
Challenging but fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: I cannot understand these reviews for the life of me. I had him in a 3000 level class a year ago and he was an amazing prof. Everybody on here calls him a tough grader but he gives good notes to anybody who gives a minimal amount of effort. This will not be your hardest class, not by a long shot. Light workload and his grading criteria is simple.

He definitely isnt the easiest prof, and his lectures arent the most interesting. But he is a prof that truly cares about his students. His standards are definitely high, but he will give you every opportunity to succeed. Definitely not a push-over, but if you have a valid reason, or there is a misunderstanding he will give you a chance to fix it.
Tries to push Trudeau's agenda too much. Wednesday class was very dry and boring. Does not know a lot about Quebec culture and people.

Mr. D. was a tough yet fair grader. He was always available after class to discuss the work and answer any questions. While he does give pop quizzes, they are easy and quick if you have attended class and done the work.
Felt like an online class. Too many group projectts and he doesnt help you if you get stuck with bad group members. Subjective grading scheme and doesnt have much feedback on tests.

Professor Beauregard is a tough professor. He grades you too harshly with very little information given. Most of the time, he lets videos play and reads from powerpoint slides. Class ends pretty fast and his pop quizzes are hilarious. But, this is not an easy class. it is a tough class.

Professor B. has alot of group projects. Be sure to go to class otherwise you'll miss the popquizzes. Not an easy A. Wish he was more clear, and less boring. Lectures drag on and he's never available after class to talk about assingments. Touph grader too.

I feel hes Very loud in class and that makes it hard to understand him. I wish he would explain things better. I feel the book is long and confusing. Assignments was tough and not sure why I got a bad mark. Not many comments in my assignment. Hes pretty funny tho.
Not clear in assignments. Just got back my mark and was serprised to find such a low grade. Did not explain the assingment clearly and is now penalizing us for it!

Mr. Beauregawd is funny and lets us watch a lot of videos. Seriously, this is an easy class if you like scifi or Lord of the Rings stuff. It's too bad the material presented is boring and dry. He wears a long scarf.

Fresh out of grad school we ave Devin Beauregard.  Not a day over 25 and hard to refer to as professor.  However, VERY easy grader and if you send him a one sentence email for clarification he will answer you in an hour with three paragraphs explaining it, he might even give you the answer.  Has "pop-quizzes" but dates get leaked easily.
